<META name=vs_defaultClientScript content=JavaScript>

<SCRIPT src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/json2/20110223/json2.js"></SCRIPT>

<SCRIPT language=javascript>

        function UpdateStatus() {
            var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
            xhr.open("POST", "QueueStatusUpdater.aspx/GetQueueStatus", true);
            xhr.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", "application/json; charset=UTF-8");
            xhr.onreadystatechange = function () {                
                if (xhr.readyState === 4 && xhr.status === 200) {     
                    try {
                        var outerResponse = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText);
                        var innerResponse = JSON.parse(outerResponse.d);
                                               
                        for (var index in innerResponse) {
                            if (innerResponse.hasOwnProperty(index)) {

                                var item = innerResponse[index];

                                parent.SetTextForQueue(item.Value, item.Key);
                            }
                        }
                    } catch (e) {
                        alert("Failed to parse JSON: " + e.message);
                    }
                }
            };
            xhr.send();

            setTimeout(UpdateStatus, 60000); // Call again after the specified delay
        }

    </SCRIPT>
</HEAD>

<HTML><HEAD id=Head1><TITLE>Abel</TITLE>
<SCRIPT language=javascript>

        var idleTime = 0; // The time in minutes since the user was last active
        var timeoutLimitInMin = 60; // minutes

        function incrementIdleTime() {
            idleTime++;

            if (idleTime >= timeoutLimitInMin) {
                window.location.href = '/niw/Logout.aspx'; // Log out the user
            }
        }

        function resetIdleTime() {
            idleTime = 0;
        }

        function addEvent(element, event, handler) {
            if (element.addEventListener) {
                // For modern browsers
                element.addEventListener(event, handler, false);
            } else if (element.attachEvent) {
                // For IE8 and earlier
                element.attachEvent('on' + event, handler);
            } else {
                // Fallback for older browsers (not common)
                element['on' + event] = handler;
            }
        }

        function subscribeToEvents() {
            addEvent(document, 'mousemove', resetIdleTime);
            addEvent(document, 'mouseover', resetIdleTime);
            addEvent(document, 'mousedown', resetIdleTime);
            addEvent(document, 'mouseup', resetIdleTime);
            addEvent(document, 'click', resetIdleTime);
            addEvent(document, 'keypress', resetIdleTime);

            // Increment the idle time counter every minute
            setInterval(incrementIdleTime, 60 * 1000);
        }

        window.onload = subscribeToEvents;
    </SCRIPT>
